---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'

const modules = [
  {
    name: 'Spectre Shell',
    detail:
      'The thin application shell for Spectre apps.',
  },
  {
    name: 'Spectre Shell Router',
    detail:
      'The routing layer that registers application routes and handles shell movement.',
  },
  {
    name: 'Spectre Shell Signals',
    detail:
      'The reactive primitives layer for local UI state inside Spectre shells.',
  },
]
---

<Layout
  title="Spectre Shell"
  description="Spectre Shell covers Spectre Shell, Spectre Shell Router, and Spectre Shell Signals as the application-shell side of the Spectre system."
>
  <section class="page-intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">Spectre Shell</p>
    <h1 class="display-headline">Application structure without framework noise.</h1>
    <p class="lead page-lead">
      Spectre Shell defines the application frame for Spectre-based apps,
      including routing and local reactive state.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-block">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Modules</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Shell, routing, and state built as one application layer.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="stack-list">
      {
        modules.map((item) => (
          <article class="stack-item">
            <p class="stack-item__kicker">Module</p>
            <h3 class="stack-item__title">{item.name}</h3>
            <p class="stack-item__copy">{item.detail}</p>
          </article>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-block section-band">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Operating model</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Move faster with stronger structure at the edges.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="two-column-copy">
      <p>
        Spectre Shell keeps the frame small and explicit. It handles startup,
        route structure, and local state without pretending the shell needs to
        become the whole app.
      </p>
      <p>
        That gives teams a stable system layer around the application so they
        can focus on behavior instead of rebuilding the same plumbing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
